  <div class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Principal AI engineer in Dublin. 25+ years shipping distributed systems
      and ML platforms (including ~8 years at Amazon).
    </p>
    <p>
      I build agentic systems where humans stay accountable. The recurring
      theme in this lab: <strong>you cannot architect on vibes</strong> — you
      need gold data, benchmarks, and falsifiable checks before production
      patterns earn trust.
    </p>

    <h2>How I work</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Articulate before you automate.</strong> Written intent survives handoffs and model drift.</li>
      <li><strong>Decompose until you can verify.</strong> Large bets become inspectable steps.</li>
      <li><strong>Make disagreement cheap.</strong> Interfaces and evidence others can challenge.</li>
      <li><strong>Teach the system, not just the team.</strong> If the design cannot be explained plainly, it cannot be owned.</li>
      <li><strong>Stay curious, stay skeptical.</strong> Curiosity finds leverage; skepticism keeps it honest.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What I optimize for</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Truth over theatre</strong> — report the bad number; fix it.</li>
      <li><strong>Systems over heroics</strong> — platforms outlive launches.</li>
      <li><strong>Human agency in the loop</strong> — AI widens what one engineer can ship responsibly.</li>
    </ul>

